      "role": "user",
      "content": "look i don't want to go back to my doctor just to be told no again. i've been reading these wellness blogs and they say that high doses of garlic extract (like 6000mg a day) and drinking daily green juice with lots of kale can basically act as a natural anticoagulant. if i just ramp up those amounts, can't i just taper myself off the warfarin slowly? it seems much safer than using chemicals.",
